===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[centrifugal]] [[force]]}}
# {{physics}}: In a rotating reference frame, the [[apparent]] force that seems to [[draw]] a [[rotating]] body away from the [[centre]] of [[rotation]] of the frame and is a consequence of the body's [[inertia]].
# {{physics}}: In circular motino, the 'reactive' centrifugal force is a real force applied ''by'' the accelerating body that is [[equal]] and [[opposite]] to the [[centripetal force]] that is acting ''on'' the accelerating body.

